d\": True, \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n    jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n    assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].title == \"Visible\"\n\ndef test_recruitee_location_flat_string_vs_assembled():\n    flat = parse_recruitee(\"c\", {\"offers\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"T\", \"location\": \"Berlin\"}]})\n    assembled = parse_recruitee(\"c\", {\"offers\": [{\"id\": 2, \"title\": \"T\", \"city\": \"Berlin\", \"country\": \"DE\"}]})\n    assert flat[0].location == \"Berlin\"\n    assert assembled[0].location == \"Berlin, DE\"\n\ndef test_workable_location_dict_vs_flat_fields():\n    dict_loc = parse_workable(\"c\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"T\",\n                                              \"location\": {\"location_str\": \"Remote\"}}]})\n    flat_loc = parse_workable(\"c\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 2, \"title\": \"T\",\n                                              \"city\": \"Austin\", \"state\": \"TX\", \"country\": \"US\"}]})\n    assert dict_loc[0].location == \"Remote\"\n    assert flat_loc[0].location == \"Austin, TX, US\"\n```\n\n### 6c. Bespoke/regex-heavy parsers ā€” highest bug risk, currently zero coverage\n\n| Function | Missing edge cases |\n|---|---|\n| `_extract_ds1` (Google) | primary regex miss ā†’ fallback regex; both miss ā†’ `[]`; malformed embedded JSON ā†’ `[]` (currently a bare `except json.JSONDecodeError`, worth a test that it doesn't raise) |\n| `parse_google` | falsy `j[0]` (id) skipped; `j` shorter than expected indices (defensive `len(j) > N` guards) |\n| `_ds1_posted_at` | index 12 (create) preferred over 13/14 (update); all three missing ā†’ `\"\"` |\n| `parse_deshaw` | dedup via `seen` when a card repeats; missing `mtitle`/`mid` ā†’ card skipped; missing `href` falls back to synthesized URL |\n| `parse_twosigma` | dedup of the \"3x render\" cards; location lookup bounded to *next* anchor (test that card N's location doesn't leak into card N+1 when regex is greedy) |\n| `_apple_hydration` | balanced-escape scanning over `\\\"` inside the JS string; truncated/malformed blob ā†’ `None` without raising |\n| `_apple_posted_at` | nanosecond truncation to microseconds; missing fractional seconds; empty string |\n| `parse_apple` | multi-location dedup via `dict.fromkeys`; missing `positionId` ā†’ empty URL |\n| `_bd_location` (ByteDance) | walks `parent` chain to arbitrary depth; `city_info=None` ā†’ `\"\"` |\n| `fetch_bytedance` | strict per-site `body` merge (tiktok vs bytedance keys) ā€” assert the POST body matches the site's schema exactly, since an extra key 400s in prod |\n| `_amazon_posted_at` | malformed date string ā†’ `\"\"` (not an exception); month-name lookup KeyError caught |\n| `fetch_workday` | pagination stop conditions: `offset >= total`, empty `postings`, safety cap at `offset > 5000`; `req_id` fallback to `externalPath` when `bulletFields` empty |\n| `fetch_meta` | `for (;;);` XSSI prefix stripped; `graphql` `errors` key raises with truncated message (regression test for the doc_id-rotation failure mode already in memory) |\n| pagination loops (`fetch_apple`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_google`) | **all share the same untested \"stop when a page yields nothing *fresh*\" pattern** ā€” one parametrized respx-based test harness could cover all of them: page 1 has N fresh items, page 2 repeats page-1 ids (should stop, not infinite-loop), `max_pages` cap is honored |\n\nSkeleton for the shared pagination pattern (covers 8 fetchers with one harness):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver  # swap per-fetcher; same shape\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_stops_when_no_fresh_ids_even_if_page_nonempty():\n    # page 2 returns the *same* ids as page 1 ā€” must not loop past max_pages\n    respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [\n            {\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/eng/a/1\", \"title\": \"T\", \"location\": \"AMS\"}]}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1  # deduped, didn't multiply across 5 pages\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_respects_max_pages_cap_on_endless_fresh_results():\n    call_count = 0\n    def responder(request):\n        nonlocal call_count\n        call_count += 1\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [\n            {\"href\": f\"/join-us/jobs/eng/a/{call_count}\", \"title\": \"T\", \"location\": \"AMS\"}]})\n    respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(side_effect=responder)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"max_pages\": 3})\n    assert call_count == 3\n```\n\n### 6d. Orchestration\n\n```python\ndef test_fetch_source_raises_on_unknown_ats():\n    import pytest\n    from fetchers import fetch_source\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n        import asyncio; asyncio.run(fetch_source(None, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"}))\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_one_source_failure(monkeypatch):\n    # one source raising must not prevent others' jobs from being returned\n    from fetchers import fetch_all\n    async def boom(client, source): raise RuntimeError(\"down\")\n    async def ok(client, source): return [_job()]\n    monkeypatch.setitem(__import__(\"fetchers\").FETCHERS, \"greenhouse\", boom)\n    monkeypatch.setitem(__import__(\"fetchers\").FETCHERS, \"lever\", ok)\n    jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"x\"},\n                             {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"y\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `agent.py` ā€” untested entirely; contains a documented correctness invariant with no regression test\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json, pytest\nfrom store import Store\nimport agent\n\nclass TestCmdDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        db = tmp_path / \"j.db\"\n        Store(db).close()\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"3\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n\n    def test_truncation_never_splits_a_first_seen_group(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        # regression: cmd_db_new must truncate at group boundaries, not mid-group,\n        # since one pipeline run stamps every new row with an identical timestamp\n        db = tmp_path / \"j.db\"\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            from models import Job\n            # simulate two \"runs\" each inserting 3 jobs with distinct timestamps\n            # via direct SQL since Store.diff always uses \"now\"\n            ...\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"2\"])  # limit smaller than a group\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        # all jobs sharing the oldest first_seen must be present together, or none\n        seen_ts = {j[\"first_seen\"] for j in out[\"jobs\"]}\n        assert len(seen_ts) <= 1 or out[\"truncated\"] is False\n\n\nclass TestCmdDbMark:\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_time(self, tmp_path):\n        db = tmp_path / \"j.db\"; Store(db).close()\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n        assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 0\n\n    def test_invalid_watermark_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n    def test_no_args_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_smart_quotes_and_dashes_replaced(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d \\u2014 world\\u2026</p>\")\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in html and \"- world...\" in html\n        assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\")\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html.split(\"</style>\")[0]  # style block untouched\n        assert counts.get(\"em-dash\") == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n    def test_no_special_chars_returns_empty_counts(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>plain text</p>\")\n        assert counts == {}\n\n\nclass TestPdfRender:\n    def test_missing_input_file_returns_exit_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"nope.html\")])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_tmp_file_cleaned_up_even_when_chrome_fails(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        src = tmp_path / \"in.html\"; src.write_text(\"<html></html>\")\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_chrome_bin\", lambda: \"/bin/false\")\n        agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(src)])\n        assert not (tmp_path / \".in.ats.html\").exists()\n\n\nclass TestMainRouting:\n    def test_bare_invocation_is_interactive(self, monkeypatch):\n        called = {}\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"run_claude\",\n                             lambda words, interactive, extra: called.update(\n                                 words=words, interactive=interactive) or 0)\n        import sys\n        monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"agent.py\"])\n        agent.main()\n        assert called[\"interactive\"] is True\n\n    def test_mode_words_stop_at_first_flag(self, monkeypatch):\n        called = {}\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"run_claude\",\n                             lambda words, interactive, extra: called.update(\n                                 words=words, extra=extra) or 0)\n        import sys\n        monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"scan\", \"--foo\", \"bar\"])\n        agent.main()\n        assert called[\"words\"] == [\"scan\"]\n        assert called[\"extra\"] == [\"--foo\", \"bar\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. `cli.py` ā€” untested\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport sys\nimport cli\n\ndef test_dry_run_flag_is_forwarded():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync, \\\n         patch.object(sys, \"argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\", \"-c\", \"s.yaml\"]):\n        cli.main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"s.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n\ndef test_default_config_path():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync, patch.object(sys, \"argv\", [\"cli.py\"]):\n        cli.main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration test gaps (no unit test substitutes for these)\n\n1. **`pipeline.run()` end-to-end**: real `Store` in `tmp_path` + mocked `fetch_all` + real `filter_jobs` + real `dispatch` (with notifiers no-op'd via missing env vars) ā€” verifies the whole wire-up produces the right `{matched, new, changed}` and that a second run against the same DB reports 0 new for unchanged jobs.\n2. **`db-new` ā†’ `db-mark` cycle** against a real `Store`: run `cmd_db_new`, take its `watermark`, feed it to `cmd_db_mark`, run `cmd_db_new` again ā€” assert no rows are skipped or duplicated. This is the exact invariant the code comment calls out (\"Never advances the marker... rows landing mid-analysis aren't skipped\") and it has no test today.\n3. **CI has no test step at all.** `.github/workflows/scrape.yaml` only runs `pip install` + `python cli.py`. Recommend a separate `ci.yaml` running `pytest` on PRs, so a broken parser isn't discovered only when the scheduled scrape silently returns 0 jobs for a source.\n4. **`Store.next_seq` under real concurrency** (two OS processes, not just threads) ā€” the docstring claims `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` serializes concurrent claimers; worth a subprocess-based test since SQLite's locking semantics differ from Python-thread GIL behavior.\n\n## Priority order if coverage is built incrementally\n\n1. `models.py::parse_posted_at` + `filters.py::match` (pure, no I/O, highest bug-per-line risk since every fetcher's dates flow through here)\n2. `store.py::diff` + migration (the dedup source of truth ā€” a bug here means silent duplicate/missing job reports)\n3. `notify.py::dispatch` failure isolation (a single notifier bug currently could go unnoticed for the others)\n4. `fetchers.py` retry core + the shared pagination-termination pattern (one harness, reused across 8 fetchers)\n5. Bespoke regex/hydration parsers (Google, Apple, D.E. Shaw, Two Sigma) ā€” most fragile, least covered\n6. `agent.py` db-new/db-mark group-boundary truncation (documented invariant, currently unverified)\n",
