        "content": "\n| Function | Missing edge cases |\n|---|---|\n| `_extract_ds1` (Google) | primary regex miss ā†’ fallback regex; both miss ā†’ `[]`; malformed embedded JSON ā†’ `[]` (currently a bare `except json.JSONDecodeError`, worth a test that it doesn't raise) |\n| `parse_google` | falsy `j[0]` (id) skipped; `j` shorter than expected indices (defensive `len(j) > N` guards) |\n| `_ds1_posted_at` | index 12 (create) preferred over 13/14 (update); all three missing ā†’ `\"\"` |\n| `parse_deshaw` | dedup via `seen` when a card repeats; missing `mtitle`/`mid` ā†’ card skipped; missing `href` falls back to synthesized URL |\n| `parse_twosigma` | dedup of the \"3x render\" cards; location lookup bounded to *next* anchor (test that card N's location doesn't leak into card N+1 when regex is greedy) |\n| `_apple_hydration` | balanced-escape scanning over `\\\"` inside the JS string; truncated/malformed blob ā†’ `None` without raising |\n| `_apple_posted_at` | nanosecond truncation to microseconds; missing fractional seconds; empty string |\n| `parse_apple` | multi-location dedup via `dict.fromkeys`; missing `positionId` ā†’ empty URL |\n| `_bd_location` (ByteDance) | walks `parent` chain to arbitrary depth; `city_info=None` ā†’ `\"\"` |\n| `fetch_bytedance` | strict per-site `body` merge (tiktok vs bytedance keys) ā€” assert the POST body matches the site's schema exactly, since an extra key 400s in prod |\n| `_amazon_posted_at` | malformed date string ā†’ `\"\"` (not an exception); month-name lookup KeyError caught |\n| `fetch_workday` | pagination stop conditions: `offset >= total`, empty `postings`, safety cap at `offset > 5000`; `req_id` fallback to `externalPath` when `bulletFields` empty |\n| `fetch_meta` | `for (;;);` XSSI prefix stripped; `graphql` `errors` key raises with truncated message (regression test for the doc_id-rotation failure mode already in memory) |\n| pagination loops (`fetch_apple`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_google`) | **all share the same untested \"stop when a page yields nothing *fresh*\" pattern** ā€” one parametrized respx-based test harness could cover all of them: page 1 has N fresh items, page 2 repeats page-1 ids (should stop, not infinite-loop), `max_pages` cap is honored |\n\nSkeleton for the shared pagination pattern (covers 8 fetchers with one harness):\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 3
