        "content": "\n1. **`pipeline.run()` end-to-end**: real `Store` in `tmp_path` + mocked `fetch_all` + real `filter_jobs` + real `dispatch` (with notifiers no-op'd via missing env vars) ā€” verifies the whole wire-up produces the right `{matched, new, changed}` and that a second run against the same DB reports 0 new for unchanged jobs.\n2. **`db-new` ā†’ `db-mark` cycle** against a real `Store`: run `cmd_db_new`, take its `watermark`, feed it to `cmd_db_mark`, run `cmd_db_new` again ā€” assert no rows are skipped or duplicated. This is the exact invariant the code comment calls out (\"Never advances the marker... rows landing mid-analysis aren't skipped\") and it has no test today.\n3. **CI has no test step at all.** `.github/workflows/scrape.yaml` only runs `pip install` + `python cli.py`. Recommend a separate `ci.yaml` running `pytest` on PRs, so a broken parser isn't discovered only when the scheduled scrape silently returns 0 jobs for a source.\n4. **`Store.next_seq` under real concurrency** (two OS processes, not just threads) ā€” the docstring claims `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` serializes concurrent claimers; worth a subprocess-based test since SQLite's locking semantics differ from Python-thread GIL behavior.\n\n",
